</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FF93FF53FF4A8842E3E6F80F" blockId="66.[151,1436,1652,2039]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="B9626913FF93FF53FF4A8842E600F82B" box="[199,330,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Mouthparts</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9626913FF93FF53FED48842E6B5F82B" box="[345,511,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Maxilla 1 palp</emphasis>
with 7 subequal, pointed or minutely serrate robust setae; 
<emphasis id="B9626913FF93FF53FB1B8843E25AF82B" box="[1174,1296,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">outer plate</emphasis>
with row of 10 variously smooth, simple of bifurcate, pointed robust setae. Mouthparts otherwise normal.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FF93FF54FF4A888AE590FF58" blockId="66.[151,1436,1652,2039]" lastBlockId="69.[151,1437,150,1149]" lastPageId="69" lastPageNumber="70" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="B9626913FF93FF53FF4A888AE670F873" box="[199,314,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Antenna 1</emphasis>
as long as pereonite 1–5 combined along dorsum, peduncle article 2 about three quarter length of 1, article 3 4/5 length of article 2, article 1 with single penicillate seta ventrally in posterior half and 2 dorsally, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FF93FF53FABF88EEE2D6F857" box="[1330,1436,2012,2038]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">flagellum</emphasis>
longer than peduncle by 1/3, of 10 articles, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FF94FF54FD0C8FA5E417FF10" box="[641,861,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">assessory flagellum</emphasis>
of 5+ articles. 
<emphasis id="B9626913FF94FF54FB8A8FA5E330FF10" box="[1031,1146,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Antenna 2</emphasis>
as long as pereonites 1–6 and 2/3 of 7 combined along dorsum, peduncular article 4 the longest, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FF94FF54FC498F89E364FF74" box="[964,1070,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">flagellum</emphasis>
of 8+ articles, articles 4–8 with single slender robust seta distally; otherwise setose.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF69E589FF92FF52FF1A8851E213F83E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6572117" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6572117" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6572117/files/figure.png" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" startId="67.[151,250,1891,1915]" targetBox="[152,1423,197,1848]" targetPageId="67">
